revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
{{Template shortcut|fl|fl.}}

<!-- Categories go at the bottom of this page and interwikis go in Wikidata. -->

== Usage ==
'''''Source:''''' 
<code><nowiki>{{fl.|1234}}</nowiki></code> ; 
<code><nowiki>{{fl.|1234–1275}}</nowiki></code> ; 
<code><nowiki>{{fl.|{{c.|1275}}}}</nowiki></code> ; 
<code><nowiki>{{fl.|1234|lk=off}}</nowiki></code>

'''''Result:''''' 
{{fl.|1234}} ; 
{{fl.|1234–1275}} ; 
{{fl.|{{c.|1275}}}} ; 
{{fl.|1234|lk=off}}

This template generates an abbreviation for [[floruit]] ("fl."); by default, it has a mouse-over [[tooltip]] explaining its meaning.

=== Parameters ===
==== First ====
This template supports an optional (first, unnamed) parameter representing a year (or range of years). For example, {{tlx|fl.|1956}} renders to give {{fl.|1956}}. This differs from <code><nowiki>{{fl.}} 1956</nowiki></code> in that <code><nowiki>{{fl.|1956}}</nowiki></code> puts a [[non-breaking space]] in between the "fl." and the number, which prevents web browsers from inserting a line break there.

==== Sortable ====
:<small>''This section is inserted from {{tlx|circa/doc}}, so the examples are with that template.''</small>
{{Circa/doc/sortable}}

==== Link ====
If the {{para|lk}} (as in "link") parameter is set to {{para|lk|off}}, then the abbreviation will be rendered as plain {{fl.|lk=off}} ; otherwise, the mark of a tooltip is displayed, {{fl.}}.
:The template previously was wikilinking instead of having a tooltip, so was used to avoid [[WP:Overlinking|overlinking]] when used repeatedly in an article.

== See also ==
* [[Floruit]]
* {{tl|Circa}}
* {{tl|Born in}}
* {{tl|Died in}}
* {{tl|Reign}}

